Q. Display all the Suppliers with the same Status as the supplier, ‘CLARK’. 

mysql> select SNAME from suppliers where STATUS = (SELECT STATUS FROM suppliers WHERE SNAME = 'Clark');
+-------+
| SNAME |
+-------+
| Smith |
| Clark |
+-------+
2 rows in set (0.00 sec)


Q. Display all the Parts which have more Weight than the Red parts. 

mysql> select PNAME FROM parts WHERE WEIGHT > ANY(SELECT WEIGHT FROM parts WHERE COLOR='Red');
+-------+
| PNAME |
+-------+
| Bolt  |
| Screw |
| Screw |
| Cog   |
+-------+
4 rows in set (0.00 sec)

Q. Display all the Parts with Weight less than the Green parts.

mysql> select PNAME FROM parts WHERE WEIGHT < ANY(SELECT WEIGHT FROM parts WHERE COLOR='Green');
+-------+
| PNAME |
+-------+
| Nut   |
| Screw |
| Cam   |
+-------+
3 rows in set (0.00 sec)

