Q. Write a query that uses a subquery to obtain all orders for the customer named Cisneros.
   output:
+------+---------+------------+------+------+
| Onum | Amt     | Odate      | Cnum | Snum |
+------+---------+------------+------+------+
| 3001 |   18.69 | 1990-10-03 | 2008 | 1007 |
| 3006 | 1098.16 | 1990-10-03 | 2008 | 1007 |
+------+---------+------------+------+------+

mysql> select * from orders where Cnum=all(select Cnum from customers where cname='Cisneros');

Q. Write a query that will find all salespeople who have no customers located in their own city.

mysql> select * from salespeople where city!=all(select city from customers);
+------+---------+-----------+------+
| snum | sname   | city      | comm |
+------+---------+-----------+------+
| 1007 | Rifkin  | Barcelona | 0.15 |
| 1003 | Axelrod | New York  | 0.10 |
+------+---------+-----------+------+
2 rows in set (0.00 sec)

Q. Select customers who have a greater rating than any of customer in Rome.
   output:
+------+----------+----------+--------+------+
| cnum | cname    | city     | rating | snum |
+------+----------+----------+--------+------+
| 2002 | Giovanni | Rome     |    200 | 1003 |
| 2003 | Liu      | San Jose |    200 | 1002 |
| 2004 | Grass    | Berlin   |    300 | 1002 |
| 2008 | Cisneros | San Jose |    300 | 1007 |
+------+----------+----------+--------+------+

mysql> select * from customers where rating>any(select rating from customers where city='Rome');

